Introduction
	Overview of Chapter
		This Chapter contains rules connected with tax avoidance.
		In particular—
			for rules about unallowable purposes and tax relief schemes andarrangements, see sections 441 to 443,
			for rules relating to credits and debits where transactions are not atarm’s length (other than credits and debits relating to exchange gains andlosses), see sections 444 to 446,
			for rules relating to credits and debits relating to exchange gains andlosses where transactions are not at arm’s length, see sections 447 to 452,
			for rules about connected parties deriving benefit from creditorrelationships, see section 453,
			for rules dealing with tax advantages from resetting interest rates, seesection 454, and
			for rules dealing with disposals of rights under creditor relationships forconsideration not fully recognised for accounting purposes, see section 455.
